{
  "texts": [
    "We run quantitative judges with increasingly worse embeddings, with X% of randomly dropped features for X ∈ {0, 50, 75, 87.5}.",
    "We report our results with LS and MN judges on rating prediction tasks in Table 4, and with BTL and BTL2 judges on preference prediction tasks in Table 5.",
    "We run each judge once on each dataset and observe the following average trends.",
    "As the number of dropped features increases, the MSE increases; and the accuracy and F1 score decrease.",
    "This validates our hypothesis that poor embeddings impact the quality of learned quantitative judges."
  ]
}